<h1>To James Otis, Sr.</h1>

<div class="docbody">
<div class="opener">
<table class="salutationBlock">
        <tr>
		<td class="salutationRight">Cambridge 6th Decr 1775.</td>
	      </tr>
      </table>
</div>
<p>Copies of the Inclosed Letter I have already written to the Governors of Rhode Island &amp; Connecticut, &amp; shall do the same to the President of the Congress in New Hampshire; as I conceive our affairs are in a very critical Situation.<a class="ptr" href="#GEWN-03-02-02-0454-fn-0001" id="GEWN-03-02-02-0454-fn-0001-ptr">1</a></p>
<p>It was mentioned to me yesterday, in conversation, that the Militia of this Government ordered in, to supply the places of the Connecticut Troops, are allowed 40/ pr Month, of 28 days. The first I highly approvd of, because I was unwilling to see any inviduous distinction in pay; the never failing consequence of which is, jealously, &amp; discordBut Sir, if the Genl Court of this Colony have resolved on the latter, you must give me leave to add, that it aims the most fatal stab to the Peace of this Army
<span class="pb" title="page number in print edition (no page scan available)" id="GEWN-03-02-02-pb-0503">[503]</span>
that ever was given; &amp; that Lord North himself, could not have devised a more effectual blow to the Recruiting Service.<a class="ptr" href="#GEWN-03-02-02-0454-fn-0002" id="GEWN-03-02-02-0454-fn-0002-ptr">2</a></p>
<p>Excuse me Sir for the strength of these expressionsif my Information is wrong (I had it from Genl Heath, who says he had it from a Member of your Court) they are altogether Improper &amp; I crave your pardon for themIf right, my Zeal in the American cause must plead my excuse. I am with great respect Sir Yr Most Obedt Hble Ser.</p>
<div class="closer">
<p class="signed">Go: Washington</p>
</div>
</div>
<div class="docback">
<div class="note-source" id="GEWN-03-02-02-0454-sn">

   <p>
<abbr title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ Autograph Letter Signed: a letter in the handwriting of, and signed by, the author ]">ALS</abbr>, <span class="ref-rep" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ Massachusetts Secretary of State, Archives Division, Boston ]">M-Ar</span>: Revolution Letters;

<abbr title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ Letter Book Copy: letters copied into a bound letter-book ]">LB</abbr>, <span class="ref-rep" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ U.S. Library of Congress, George Washington Papers, Washington, D.C. ]">DLC:GW</span>;

<abbr title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ Handwritten copies in one of the bound volumes used by the team of clerks on GW's headquarters staff who worked from 1781-83 under the direction of Lt. Col. Richard Varick to record correspondence, orders, instructions, and related items from GWs Revolutionary War papers ]">Varick transcript</abbr>, <span class="ref-rep" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ U.S. Library of Congress, George Washington Papers, Washington, D.C. ]">DLC:GW</span>.
</p>

</div>
<div id="fn" class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#GEWN-03-02-02-0454-fn-0001-ptr" id="GEWN-03-02-02-0454-fn-0001">1</a>

   <p>See <a href="default.xqy?keys=GEWN-print-03-02-02-0443" class="document">Circular to the New England Governments, 5 Dec. 1775</a>.</p>

</div>
<div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#GEWN-03-02-02-0454-fn-0002-ptr" id="GEWN-03-02-02-0454-fn-0002">2</a>

   <p>For the militia reinforcements from Massachusetts and the dispute over paying troops by lunar months instead of calendar months, see <a href="default.xqy?keys=GEWN-print-03-02-02-0411&amp;expandNote=GEWN-03-02-02-0411-fn-0001#GEWN-03-02-02-0411-fn-0001" class="document">GW to the Massachusetts General Court, 29 Nov. 1775, nn. 1</a> and <a href="default.xqy?keys=GEWN-print-03-02-02-0411&amp;expandNote=GEWN-03-02-02-0411-fn-0002#GEWN-03-02-02-0411-fn-0002" class="document">2</a>. For the response to this letter of 6 Dec., see the <a href="default.xqy?keys=GEWN-print-03-02-02-0459" class="document">Massachusetts General Court to GW, 7 Dec. 1775</a>.</p>

</div>
